OL,6,FThose taking part in the vigil will be
OL,7,Fgiven a cockle shell to take away as a
OL,8,Fpermanent reminder of the ongoing
OL,9,Ffight against modern slavery and the
OL,10,Flives that were lost.
OL,12,FBishop of Blackburn, the Rt Rev.
OL,13,FPhilip North said: "This will be a
OL,14,Fsolemn moment for the community in
OL,15,FMorecambe as we join together to
OL,16,Fremember the innocent lives lost to
OL,17,Fgreed and slavery in the waters of
OL,18,FMorecambe Bay.
